18, 2020 at 10:36 a.m.NEW YORK (AP) — New York's daily toll of coronavirus deaths hit its lowest point in more than two weeks, but Gov.
Here are the latest coronavirus developments in New York:DECLINING DEATH TOLLThe daily increase in coronavirus deaths in New York state has dropped under 550 for the first time in over two weeks as hospitalizations continue to decline, Cuomo said Saturday.
The state total doesn’t include more than 4,000 New York City deaths that were blamed on the virus on death certificates but weren’t confirmed by a lab test.
Officials have said an estimated half-million city residents are out of work or likely to lose their jobs soon.
Even before the crisis, 1.2 million city residents struggled at times to feed themselves.